{"questionId":"3001269","questionHtml":"<p>Use calculus to find the minimum value of the expression <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></math>, justifying that this value is a minimum.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempts to solve their&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo> </mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>⇒</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math></p>\n<p>(when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>,) <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math> (when <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn></math>)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>hence <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></math> has a minimum value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>R1</strong></em> for either ‘<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>’ or a graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></mfrac><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math> or ‘the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></math> is concave-up’. Do not award <em><strong>R1</strong></em> if the second derivative is incorrect.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&lt;</mo><mo>)</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>hence <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></math> has a minimum value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award<em><strong> R1R1</strong></em> for either a clearly labelled sign diagram/table (accept correct numerical values) or the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>x</mi></mfrac></math> with sign change in gradient indicated.</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award a maximum of <em><strong>A0(M1)A1A0R1</strong></em> or <em><strong>A0(M1)A1R0R1</strong></em> if no symbolic derivatives are seen.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"3001269","referenceCode":"23M.3.AHL.TZ2.1b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Use calculus to find the minimum value of the expression x-ln x, justifying that this value is a minimum.","paper":"3","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 5 —Calculus","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.6—Differentiating polynomials n E Q. Chain, product and quotient rules","Topic 5 —Calculus","SL 5.8—Testing for max and min, optimisation. Points of inflexion","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.9—Exponential and logarithmic functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}